<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="DART Rate">
  <data key="d0">DART Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">DART Rate measures injuries or illnesses resulting in days away from work, restricted duty, or job transfer, calculated over five calendar years.&lt;SEP&gt;DART Rate is calculated by multiplying the number of DART incidents by 200,000 and dividing by total employee labor hours, used to assess safety performance over five calendar years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="TCR Rate">
  <data key="d0">TCR Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">TCR Rate measures total recordable cases including death, days away, restricted work, medical treatment beyond first aid, or loss of consciousness, calculated over five calendar years.&lt;SEP&gt;TCR Rate is calculated by multiplying the number of TCR incidents by 200,000 and dividing by total employee labor hours, requiring submission of data for five previous calendar years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Safety Management System (SMS)">
  <data key="d0">Safety Management System (SMS)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Safety Management System (SMS) involves management leadership, employee involvement, hazard prevention, control, worksite analysis, and safety training, benchmarked against standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Safety Management System (SMS) involves management/leadership involvement, employee involvement, hazard prevention, hazard control, worksite analysis, and safety training, benchmarked against standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Approach to Safety">
  <data key="d0">Technical Approach to Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">submission_instruction</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Approach to Safety requires a narrative limited to two single-sided pages describing SMS implementation, subcontractor selection, oversight processes, and safety compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="OSHA">
  <data key="d0">OSHA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">OSHA is a source of public data reviewed by the Government for safety information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVFAC">
  <data key="d0">NAVFAC</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">NAVFAC maintains the Contractor Incident Reporting System (CIRS) as a source of safety data.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC establishes command-wide small business subcontracting targets based on percentages of total planned subcontract dollars.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC sets command-wide small business subcontracting targets including 40% for Small Business and others.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC is referenced in documents including NAVFAC Maximo procedures, instructions like NAVFACINST 11230.1, and asset naming conventions.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC is the Naval Facilities Engineering Systems Command responsible for the Maximo data system, contractor incident reporting, and performance assessments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Incident Reporting System (CIRS)">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Incident Reporting System (CIRS)</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Incident Reporting System (CIRS) is NAVFAC's system for reporting contractor incidents, reviewed by the Government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS)">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS)</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS) provides past performance evaluations to be submitted if available for projects.&lt;SEP&gt;Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS) is a government system for evaluating contractor performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Contract Management System (eCMS)">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Contract Management System (eCMS)</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Contract Management System (eCMS) is a Government internal source of information reviewed for safety and performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Electronic Contract Management System (eCMS) is a system used for contract management and review by the government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance evaluates recency, relevancy, and quality of recent projects, using CPARS, PPQ, and other sources to assess successful completion, timeliness, quality, and cooperation.&lt;SEP&gt;Past Performance is evaluated based on relevancy definitions for projects similar in size, scope, and complexity to the RFP requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance Questionnaire (PPQ)">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance Questionnaire (PPQ)</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance Questionnaire (PPQ) is provided for clients to complete if no CPARS is available, to be submitted with proposals for relevant projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System (FAPIIS)">
  <data key="d0">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System (FAPIIS)</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System (FAPIIS) is a database source for past performance information used in evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Subcontract Reporting System (eSRS)">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System (eSRS)</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System (eSRS) is a database source for past performance information reviewed by the Government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Courtney Peterson">
  <data key="d0">Courtney Peterson</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Courtney Peterson is a Government point of contact for submitting PPQs via email.&lt;SEP&gt;Courtney Peterson is the Contract Specialist for pre-award inquiries in the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;Courtney Peterson is a contact for submitting site visit access forms at courtney.j.peterson3.civ@us.navy.mil.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Cari Fiebach">
  <data key="d0">Cari Fiebach</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Cari Fiebach is a Government point of contact for submitting PPQs via email.&lt;SEP&gt;Cari Fiebach is a contact for submitting site visit access forms at cari.l.fiebach.civ@us.navy.mil.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.217-5">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.217-5</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.217-5 is the Evaluation of Options clause incorporated by reference, effective July 1990.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Very Low Risk">
  <data key="d0">Very Low Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Very Low Risk for DART is less than 1.0 and for TCR less than 2.49, indicating strong safety performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Low Risk">
  <data key="d0">Low Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Low Risk for DART is from 1.0 to 1.99 and for TCR from 2.5 to 3.49, assessed in safety evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Moderate Risk">
  <data key="d0">Moderate Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Moderate Risk for DART is from 2.0 to 2.99 and for TCR from 3.5 to 4.49, requiring explanations for negative trends.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="High Risk">
  <data key="d0">High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High Risk for DART is from 3.0 to 4.0 and for TCR from 4.5 to 5.99, potentially indicating weaknesses without explanation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Extremely High Risk">
  <data key="d0">Extremely High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Extremely High Risk for DART is greater than 4.0 and for TCR greater than 6.0, requiring detailed corrective actions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Corporate Experience">
  <data key="d0">Corporate Experience</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Corporate Experience is Factor 1, requiring submission of two to five examples of recent relevant projects to assess capability and risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Corporate Experience is Factor 1 requiring offerors to identify and describe recent, relevant projects for determining relevancy in past performance evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Contract Management Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Contract Management Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Contract Management Agency is a source of past performance information, including data from databases and interviews with program managers, contracting officers, and fee determining officials.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment D">
  <data key="d0">Attachment D</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment D is the first page of the Past Performance Questionnaire providing contract and client information for projects when a completed PPQ cannot be obtained before proposal closing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv)">
  <data key="d0">FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv)</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv) governs the evaluation of past performance when information is unavailable, assigning a neutral rating.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Subcontractors">
  <data key="d0">Subcontractors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Subcontractors are entities selected and overseen by the offeror for safety compliance throughout contract performance, including evaluation processes and management plans.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003 is the solicitation number for the Base Operations Support contract.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation or contract identifier referenced throughout the clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the contract identifier that incorporates various FAR and DFARS clauses by reference and full text.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the contract number referenced throughout the document for administration and clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the contract identifier for a performance-based contract providing base operations support services at specified naval facilities.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the identifier for the solicitation document referenced throughout the text.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation and contract identifier referenced in the document pages and sections.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation identifier under which various facility inventory documents and Section K representations are provided.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Naval Station Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Naval Station Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Naval Station Mayport is a naval facility in Jacksonville, Florida, requiring Base Operations Support services.&lt;SEP&gt;Naval Station Mayport is located in Jacksonville, Florida, and is a primary site for base operations support services under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Jacksonville, Florida">
  <data key="d0">Jacksonville, Florida</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Jacksonville, Florida is the location hosting Naval Station Mayport and Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island">
  <data key="d0">Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville, Florida is one of the primary locations for work performance under the contract, along with outlying areas supported by these commands.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island is a support facility in Jacksonville, Florida, primarily serviced for custodial, pest control, integrated solid waste management, and grounds maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island is located in Jacksonville, Florida, and receives support from base operations services under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Base Operations Support">
  <data key="d0">Base Operations Support</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Base Operations Support encompasses services including port operations, facility management, facility investment, custodial, pest control, integrated solid waste management, swimming pools, grounds maintenance, landscaping, utilities management, electrical, wastewater, steam, water, transportation, and environmental support.&lt;SEP&gt;Base Operations Support encompasses services like port operations, facility investment, electrical, and water systems as defined in relevant projects.&lt;SEP&gt;Base Operations Support services encompass technical annexes like Port Operations, Facility Investment, Electrical, Water, and BSVE, requiring demonstration of at least three plus one other in relevant projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Jacobs Technology Inc.">
  <data key="d0">Jacobs Technology Inc.</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Jacobs Technology Inc. is the previous contractor for contract N69450-18-D-1800, providing Base Operations Support services with specified periods of performance and costs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Performance Work Statement">
  <data key="d0">Performance Work Statement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Performance Work Statement outlines the requirements for Base Operations Support services, including labor, supervision, management, tools, materials, equipment, facilities, transportation, incidental engineering, and other necessary items.&lt;SEP&gt;The Performance Work Statement describes the scope of services in the RFP, including size, scope, and complexity for relevant projects.&lt;SEP&gt;Performance Work Statement outlines the requirements for recurring and non-recurring base operations support services and is applicable to all option line items.&lt;SEP&gt;The Performance Work Statement describes the services, specifications, objectives, and standards for the contract, used to define relevant project similarity.&lt;SEP&gt;Performance Work Statement contains performance objectives that offerors should not merely parrot in proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="NAICS Code 561210">
  <data key="d0">NAICS Code 561210</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">NAICS Code 561210 classifies the solicitation under Facilities Support Services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="N69450-18-D-1800">
  <data key="d0">N69450-18-D-1800</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N69450-18-D-1800 is the prior contract for Base Operations Support services, set to expire on 31 December 2026, with detailed periods of performance and costs totaling $211,045,432.21.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Section A">
  <data key="d0">Section A</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section A covers the solicitation/contract form, type of contract, service requirements, competition requirement, NAICS code, and prior contract information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="Section B">
  <data key="d0">Section B</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section B details supplies or services and prices or costs, including pricing of CLINs, maximum NTE, minimum guarantee, unit price adjustments, and specific line items for recurring and non-recurring work.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains pricing information submitted within the proposal, evaluated for inconsistencies with Section J ELIN attachment.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B of the solicitation requires completion for pricing submittal, including CLIN details.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains line item details for pricing in the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains the schedule of unit price tasks and pre-priced line items supported by Section J ELINs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
<node id="CLIN 0001">
  <data key="d0">CLIN 0001</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">CLIN 0001 represents the base period recurring firm fixed price Base Operations Support services, supported by ELINs A001 through A014, serving as the overall guaranteed minimum.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836281</data>
</node>
