<node id="Service Contract Labor Standards">
  <data key="d0">Service Contract Labor Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Service Contract Labor Standards apply to wage determinations and price adjustments for covered employees in recurring work.&lt;SEP&gt;Service Contract Labor Standards, governed by 29 CFR Part 4, requires compliance with wages and fringe benefits for service employees under the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Service Contract Labor Standards is a statute referenced in wage determinations, with section 4(c) applying to bargaining unit work regardless of whether performed by prime contractor or subcontractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836282</data>
</node>
<node id="Construction Wage Rate Requirements">
  <data key="d0">Construction Wage Rate Requirements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Construction Wage Rate Requirements apply to wage determinations and price adjustments for covered employees in recurring work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836282</data>
</node>
<node id="Collective Bargaining Agreements">
  <data key="d0">Collective Bargaining Agreements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Collective Bargaining Agreements from the previous service provider are incorporated into the contract for wage adjustments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Minimum Guarantee">
  <data key="d0">Minimum Guarantee</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Minimum Guarantee applies to CLIN 0001 for the base period recurring work, with no application to option periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Maximum NTE">
  <data key="d0">Maximum NTE</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Maximum Not To Exceed value limits orders for each ordering period and the overall contract, adjustable by modification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="DPAS">
  <data key="d0">DPAS</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">The contract is a rated order under DPAS per 15 CFR 7900.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Government">
  <data key="d0">Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Government is the entity that may extend services or contract terms, evaluate offers with preferences, and limit obligations for incrementally funded items.&lt;SEP&gt;The Government estimates contractor overhead, profit rates, and material costs, and receives liquidated damages for nonperformance or unsatisfactory performance under the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;The Government owns and controls historical resources, provides facilities for contract use, and inspects contractor performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor">
  <data key="d0">Contractor</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor is required to complete orders post-effective period, rerepresent status, certify indirect costs, and perform up to funded amounts in incrementally funded contracts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contractor performs services under the contract and is subject to liquidated damages for delays or failure to perform required services.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contractor performs all requirements, including protecting resources, registering on FedMall, and reporting to the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Liquidated Damages">
  <data key="d0">Liquidated Damages</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Liquidated damages compensate the Government for administrative costs and expenses from nonperformed or unsatisfactory performance, calculated in accordance with Section H.&lt;SEP&gt;Liquidated damages compensate for administrative costs from unsatisfactory or non-performed work, assessed at 10% of defect value.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H">
  <data key="d0">Section H</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H includes the special requirement titled Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services, used for calculating liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services">
  <data key="d0">Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">This special requirement in Section H outlines consequences for the Contractor's failure to perform required services, including liquidated damages calculation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section I - Contract Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Section I - Contract Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section I lists FAR and DFARS clauses incorporated by reference and provides full text for specific clauses applicable to the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR">
  <data key="d0">FAR</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Federal Acquisition Regulation provides clauses incorporated by reference and full text in Section I of the contract, covering topics such as definitions, gratuities, and liquidated damages.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR is the Federal Acquisition Regulation, which includes clauses like 52.242-15 and 52.247-34 incorporated by reference in the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS">
  <data key="d0">DFARS</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement provides clauses incorporated by reference in Section I of the contract, addressing defense-specific requirements like compensation of former DoD officials and safeguarding covered defense information.&lt;SEP&gt;DFARS is the Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement, which includes clauses incorporated by reference and full text in the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer provides written approval for the contract, making it binding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.204-1 Approval Of Contract">
  <data key="d0">52.204-1 Approval Of Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause requires written approval by the NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer for the contract to be binding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.211-11 Liquidated Damages-Supplies, Services, Or Research And Development">
  <data key="d0">52.211-11 Liquidated Damages-Supplies, Services, Or Research And Development</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause specifies that the Contractor pays liquidated damages of $ per calendar day of delay for failure to deliver supplies or perform services within the time specified in the contract, with liability continuing upon termination and excusable delays defined by reference to other clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.215-21 Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications">
  <data key="d0">52.215-21 Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause, including Alternates I and III, requires the Contractor to submit certified cost or pricing data and data other than certified cost or pricing data in specified formats for modifications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.216-18 Ordering">
  <data key="d0">52.216-18 Ordering</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause governs the issuance of delivery orders or task orders for supplies and services under the contract, specifying methods of issuance and precedence.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.216-19 Order Limitations">
  <data key="d0">52.216-19 Order Limitations</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause sets minimum and maximum order limits for supplies or services, including $2,500 minimum and up to $1,000,000 maximum for combinations of items.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.216-22 Indefinite Quantity">
  <data key="d0">52.216-22 Indefinite Quantity</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause establishes the contract as indefinite-quantity, with estimated quantities, minimum and maximum orders, and requirements for delivery or performance upon order.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-8 Option To Extend Services">
  <data key="d0">52.217-8 Option To Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause allows the Government to extend services up to 6 months at specified rates, exercisable by written notice prior to contract expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-9 Option To Extend The Term Of The Contract">
  <data key="d0">52.217-9 Option To Extend The Term Of The Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause permits the Government to extend the contract term up to 96 months total, with preliminary notice required at least 30 days before expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-4 Notice Of Price Evaluation Preference For Hubzone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">52.219-4 Notice Of Price Evaluation Preference For Hubzone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause provides a 10 percent price evaluation preference for offers from HUBZone small business concerns that have not waived the preference.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Default-Fixed-Price Supply And Service Clause">
  <data key="d0">Default-Fixed-Price Supply And Service Clause</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Default-Fixed-Price Supply And Service clause defines conditions for termination and excusable delays, referenced in the liquidated damages clause.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Termination Clause">
  <data key="d0">Termination Clause</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Termination clause addresses excess costs of repurchase in addition to liquidated damages upon contract termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HUBZone small business concerns receive a 10 percent price evaluation preference for offers unless the preference is waived.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">The Schedule specifies the supplies and services, estimated quantities, ordering authorities, and period from contract award to completion date.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="WAWF">
  <data key="d0">WAWF</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">WAWF is a system for electronic invoicing and receiving reports, with contact information provided for assistance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.1">
  <data key="d0">Section H.1</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.1 addresses the protection and reporting of historical and archaeological resources discovered during work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Historical And Archaeological Resources">
  <data key="d0">Historical And Archaeological Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical and archaeological resources include items and human skeletal remains that must be protected and reported to the Contracting Officer.&lt;SEP&gt;Historical And Archaeological Resources must be protected in-place, reported immediately upon discovery, with work stopped in the area until directed by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Contracting Officer is responsible for exercising options, requiring rerepresentations, and establishing unilateral rates if certifications are not submitted.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer directs work resumption after discoveries and retains ownership over resources.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer specifies time limits for negotiating the Small Business Subcontracting Plan and determines eligibility for contract award.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting Officer is the government representative who schedules and participates in the pre-performance conference to discuss work administration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.2">
  <data key="d0">Section H.2</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.2 outlines requirements for Fedmall registration, catalog upload, and processing of GCPC orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Fedmall">
  <data key="d0">Fedmall</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Fedmall is a U.S. Government-owned web-based ordering system for DoD and Federal activities to search and order goods and services.&lt;SEP&gt;Fedmall is a U.S. Government web-based ordering system for goods and services, requiring contractor registration, catalog upload, and acceptance of electronic GCPC orders for IQ services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Supplier Registration">
  <data key="d0">Supplier Registration</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Supplier Registration is required for contractors to upload contract catalogs to Fedmall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program">
  <data key="d0">Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program involves issuing orders through Fedmall for IQ pre-priced line item services without additional fees.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="IQ Pre-Priced Line Item Services">
  <data key="d0">IQ Pre-Priced Line Item Services</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">IQ pre-priced line item services are offered to authorized Government personnel via GCPC orders through Fedmall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="External Certification Authority Program">
  <data key="d0">External Certification Authority Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The External Certification Authority Program issues DoD-approved certificates for secure communication and authentication to DoD systems.&lt;SEP&gt;External Certification Authority Program is the DoD initiative providing approved certificates to contractors for secure communication and authentication to DoD systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="PGP Personal Software">
  <data key="d0">PGP Personal Software</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">PGP Personal Software or comparable solution is required for decrypting order notification emails from Fedmall using 128-bit encryption.&lt;SEP&gt;PGP Personal Software is required for contractors to decrypt 128-bit encrypted order notification emails from FedMall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="ECA Certificate">
  <data key="d0">ECA Certificate</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">A DoD-approved ECA certificate must be purchased, installed, and maintained for secure interactions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="ELIN">
  <data key="d0">ELIN</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">ELINs are Equipment Line Item Numbers available for ordering via Fedmall, including various temporary services and cleanups.&lt;SEP&gt;ELIN refers to Exhibit Line Item Numbers used in pricing spreadsheet data submission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Blount Island">
  <data key="d0">Blount Island</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Blount Island is referenced in ELIN X718 for shoreline cleanup services.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is referenced in base access forms, site maps, and facility inventories for MCSF-BI.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the site specified in the shoreline cleanup plan and map under grounds maintenance for Mcsf-Bi.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.3">
  <data key="d0">Section H.3</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.3 authorizes additional methods for issuing delivery or task orders, including oral, facsimile, and electronic commerce.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clause 52.216-18">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clause 52.216-18</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clause 52.216-18 Ordering authorizes methods for issuance of delivery or task orders under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.4">
  <data key="d0">Section H.4</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.4 incorporates FAR Clause 52.216-19 Order Limitations, which is not applicable to recurring work, Fedmall orders, or GCPC Program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clause 52.216-19">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clause 52.216-19</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clause 52.216-19 Order Limitations sets limits on orders but excludes certain programs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.5">
  <data key="d0">Section H.5</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.5 specifies that the contract includes some construction work subject to labor standards and lists applicable clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Construction Work">
  <data key="d0">Construction Work</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Construction work includes major repair, minor construction, demolition, and efforts under Non-Recurring ELINs, subject to specific FAR clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Miller Act">
  <data key="d0">Miller Act</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Miller Act requires performance and payment bonds for construction task orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.6">
  <data key="d0">Section H.6</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.6 incorporates FAR Clause 52.211-10 for commencement, prosecution, and completion of work, applicable to task orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clause 52.211-10">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clause 52.211-10</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clause 52.211-10 Commencement, Prosecution, And Completion Of Work sets timelines for contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.7">
  <data key="d0">Section H.7</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.7 requires contractors to furnish and display identification for employees as directed by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Employee Identification">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Employee Identification</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor employee identification must be displayed at all times, including in meetings and correspondence.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.8">
  <data key="d0">Section H.8</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.8 uses unit prices for deductions under FAR 52.246-4 Inspection Of Services - Fixed-Price and H.12.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clause 52.246-4">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clause 52.246-4</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clause 52.246-4 Inspection Of Services - Fixed-Price serves as basis for deductions in performance assessments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.9">
  <data key="d0">Section H.9</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.9 states that Government property is not included, but facilities, equipment, and utilities are available in "as is" condition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Government Property">
  <data key="d0">Government Property</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Government property excludes items in the contract but includes available facilities and utilities for contract use only.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.10">
  <data key="d0">Section H.10</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.10 limits authority to bind the Government to the Contracting Officer only.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Authority">
  <data key="d0">Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Authority to modify the contract is exclusively held by the Contracting Officer, excluding actions by other personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.11">
  <data key="d0">Section H.11</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.11 governs substitutions of key personnel identified in Section C, requiring comparable qualifications and no price changes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Key Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Key Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Key personnel are identified in Section C, with substitutions needing Contracting Officer approval within 15 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836283</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.12">
  <data key="d0">Section H.12</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.12 outlines consequences for failure to perform, including re-performance, payment withholding, and liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Watchstanding Services">
  <data key="d0">Watchstanding Services</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Watchstanding services require qualified personnel; failures lead to withholdings and potential liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.13">
  <data key="d0">Section H.13</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.13 provides methods for estimating non-performed work costs when Schedule prices are unavailable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Non-Performed Work Estimation">
  <data key="d0">Non-Performed Work Estimation</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Non-performed work estimation uses wage rates, overhead, profit, and material costs for deductions and liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Section I">
  <data key="d0">Section I</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section I incorporates various FAR clauses by reference, including definitions, gratuities, and anti-kickback procedures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clauses">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clauses listed include 52.202-1 Definitions, 52.203-3 Gratuities, and others up to 52.209-6 Protecting The Government's Interest.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Department Of Defense">
  <data key="d0">Department Of Defense</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Department of Defense operates Fedmall and establishes programs like ECA for contractor interactions.&lt;SEP&gt;Department Of Defense is the entity that operates FedMall and the External Certification Authority Program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Logistics Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Logistics Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Defense Logistics Agency provides information on Fedmall and supplier registration.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Logistics Agency provides the specified supplies available for acquisition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="DD 1155">
  <data key="d0">DD 1155</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">DD 1155 is an approved form for orders that the contractor must track quantities and report monthly and year-to-date to the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Section C">
  <data key="d0">Section C</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section C specifies the work locations under the solicitation and resulting contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C provides the description, specifications, and statement of work for the performance-based contract, including attachments posted on SAM.gov.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C identifies the key personnel for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Section F">
  <data key="d0">Section F</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section F covers deliveries or performance, including location, contract term, transition period, pre-performance conference, and deliverables.&lt;SEP&gt;Section F specifies the delivery schedule, including notifications for catalog uploads to the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Section J">
  <data key="d0">Section J</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section J includes the ELIN attachment, used in evaluating proposal pricing for inconsistencies.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J is the List of Attachments that includes documents, exhibits, and other attachments posted on the SAM website at https://sam.gov/ with the solicitation, covering acquisition and technical documents.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J contains the Exhibit Line Item Number (ELIN) Pricing Attachment with multiple worksheets for completion.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J includes attachments like Attachment J-0200000-17 for Exhibit Line Item Numbers in pricing.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J provides ELINs that support the line items in Section B for ordering via FedMall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment J-0200000-08">
  <data key="d0">Attachment J-0200000-08</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment J-0200000-08 lists the Government-owned facilities, equipment, and utilities available to the contractor in as-is condition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS 211.106">
  <data key="d0">DFARS 211.106</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 211.106 requires the contractor to furnish and display identification for employees as contractor personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.211-11">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.211-11</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.211-11 Liquidated Damages - Supplies, Services, or Research and Development allows assessment of damages for unsatisfactory or non-performed work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.222-42">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.222-42</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.222-42 Statement of Equivalent Rate for Federal Hires is used to compute costs when Government employees perform non-performed work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.202-1">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.202-1</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.202-1 Definitions provides standard definitions incorporated by reference in Section I.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Temporary HVAC 100 Ton Chiller">
  <data key="d0">Temporary HVAC 100 Ton Chiller</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Temporary HVAC 100 ton chiller is described under ELIN X711 for ordering via FedMall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="Blount Island Shoreline Cleanup">
  <data key="d0">Blount Island Shoreline Cleanup</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Blount Island shoreline cleanup is described under ELIN X718 for ordering via FedMall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="WAWF Helpdesk">
  <data key="d0">WAWF Helpdesk</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">WAWF Helpdesk provides assistance at 866-618-5988 for issues with the WAWF system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.223-2">
  <data key="d0">52.223-2</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.223-2 is a clause titled Reporting of Biobased Products Under Service and Construction Contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.223-4">
  <data key="d0">52.223-4</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.223-4 is a provision titled Recovered Material Certification, applying to solicitations for or specifying the use of EPA-designated items.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.223-22">
  <data key="d0">52.223-22</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.223-22 is a provision titled Public Disclosure of Greenhouse Gas Emissions and Reduction Goals-Representation, applying to solicitations including the provision at 52.204-7.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.225-2">
  <data key="d0">52.225-2</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.225-2 is a provision titled Buy American Certificate, applying to solicitations containing the clause at 52.225-1.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.225-4">
  <data key="d0">52.225-4</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.225-4 is a provision titled Buy American-Free Trade Agreements-Israeli Trade Act Certificate, with basic, Alternate II, and Alternate III versions applying based on acquisition value thresholds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.225-6">
  <data key="d0">52.225-6</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.225-6 is a provision titled Trade Agreements Certificate, applying to solicitations containing the clause at 52.225-5.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.225-20">
  <data key="d0">52.225-20</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.225-20 is a provision titled Prohibition on Conducting Restricted Business Operations in Sudan-Certification, applying to all solicitations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.225-25">
  <data key="d0">52.225-25</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.225-25 is a provision titled Prohibition on Contracting with Entities Engaging in Certain Activities or Transactions Relating to Iran-Representation and Certifications, applying to all solicitations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.226-2">
  <data key="d0">52.226-2</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.226-2 is a provision titled Historically Black College or University and Minority Institution Representation, applying to solicitations for research, studies, supplies, or services normally acquired from higher educational institutions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.204-17">
  <data key="d0">52.204-17</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.204-17 is a representation or certification titled Ownership or Control of Offeror, applicable as indicated by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.204-20">
  <data key="d0">52.204-20</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.204-20 is a representation or certification titled Predecessor of Offeror, applicable as indicated by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
<node id="52.222-18">
  <data key="d0">52.222-18</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.222-18 is a certification titled Certification Regarding Knowledge of Child Labor for Listed End Products, applicable as indicated by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836284</data>
</node>
