  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">E/U/R Work Orders refer to Emergency, Urgent, and Routine service orders that must be performed according to applicable annexes and sub-annexes with an efficient and effective approach.&lt;SEP&gt;E/U/R Work Orders refer to Emergency, Urgent, and Routine work orders or service orders required across multiple annexes and sub-annexes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
