  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Training Pools (1503040 Other) is a sub-annex under Facilities Support, addressed in the technical approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="General Information">
  <data key="d0">General Information</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">General Information (0100000) is an annex not considered towards the minimum technical annex requirement for relevant projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Management and Administration">
  <data key="d0">Management and Administration</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Management and Administration (0200000) is an annex not counted towards the minimum one other technical annex for demonstrating relevant projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Civil Engineering Support Equipment">
  <data key="d0">Civil Engineering Support Equipment</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Civil Engineering Support Equipment (CESE) is maintained and repaired under BSVE requirements similar to the RFP.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Weight Handling Equipment">
  <data key="d0">Weight Handling Equipment</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Weight Handling Equipment (WHE) involves operations, maintenance, and repair under BSVE, aligned with RFP specifications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="RS Means Facilities Maintenance &amp; Repair Cost Data">
  <data key="d0">RS Means Facilities Maintenance &amp; Repair Cost Data</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">RS Means Facilities Maintenance &amp; Repair Cost Data is a source used in developing the Basis of Estimate for labor hours and costs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Whitestone Building and Repair Cost Reference">
  <data key="d0">Whitestone Building and Repair Cost Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Whitestone Building and Repair Cost Reference is an estimate data source for performing specification items in the Basis of Estimate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport is the organization responsible for inspection and acceptance at the specified location in Mayport, Florida.&lt;SEP&gt;Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport is the organization responsible for contract administration and inspection at the specified location in Mayport, FL.&lt;SEP&gt;Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport is the organization responsible for inspection and acceptance of services at Building 1966, Bon Homme Richard St, Mayport, FL 32228-0073, with DoDAAC N46134.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Mayport, Fl">
  <data key="d0">Mayport, Fl</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Mayport, Fl is the location for inspection and acceptance, including Building 1966 on Bon Homme Richard Street with zip code 32228-0073.&lt;SEP&gt;Mayport, FL 32228-0073 is the place of performance and address for the contract activities, including Building 1966 on Bon Homme Richard St.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="United States">
  <data key="d0">United States</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">United States is the country code USA associated with the inspection and acceptance location.&lt;SEP&gt;United States is the country code and location for the contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Inspector Of Record, Pwd Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Inspector Of Record, Pwd Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Inspector Of Record, Pwd Mayport is the contact for inspection with telephone number 904-270-6716.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville, Florida is one of the primary locations for work performance under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003 Sectionf.Pdf">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003 Sectionf.Pdf</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003 Sectionf.Pdf is the attachment file for Section F posted on the SAM website.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Dod AAC N46134">
  <data key="d0">Dod AAC N46134</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Dod AAC N46134 is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code associated with the place of performance and inspection location.&lt;SEP&gt;Dod AAC N46134 is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code used for the place of performance in the option line items.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Term">
  <data key="d0">Contract Term</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract Term specifies an initial one-year performance period starting 01 January 2027, with seven one-year option periods totaling eight years, and potential extensions under FAR 52.217-8 and FAR 52.217-9.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Transition Period">
  <data key="d0">Transition Period</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Transition Period allows 90 days for mobilization post-award by 30 September 2026 and demobilization 90 days prior to contract completion to support the follow-on contractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Performance Conference">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Performance Conference</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-Performance Conference is a meeting within 30 days of contract award with the Contracting Officer to discuss scheduling and work administration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Deliverables">
  <data key="d0">Deliverables</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Deliverables are to be submitted electronically in Microsoft Office 365 compatible format via email or CD-ROM to points of contact in Section F attachment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Option Line Item">
  <data key="d0">Option Line Item</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Option Line Item refers to various contract line items such as 0007 through 0027, each with inspection and acceptance at the same location and instructions referencing Section F.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Delivery Period">
  <data key="d0">Delivery Period</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Delivery Period outlines schedules for line items from 01 January 2027 to 31 December 2031, each for one year at the place of performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-9">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-9</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-9 provides the regulatory authority for the Government to extend the term of the contract in accordance with its provisions incorporated into the resulting contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-8">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-8</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-8 provides the regulatory authority to extend contract performance up to an additional six months beyond the established 96 months.&lt;SEP&gt;Far 52.217-8 is a Federal Acquisition Regulation clause for option to extend services, applied to specific option periods in Clin 0025, Clin 0026, and Clin 0027.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="System For Award Management">
  <data key="d0">System For Award Management</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">System For Award Management hosts the SAM website at sam.gov where the files for Section F are provided as attachments.&lt;SEP&gt;System For Award Management is the registry at https://www.sam.gov where contractors designate an electronic business point of contact for WAWF access.&lt;SEP&gt;System For Award Management is the registration system where offerors complete individual representations and certifications applicable to the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Microsoft Office 365">
  <data key="d0">Microsoft Office 365</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Microsoft Office 365 is the most recent Government-installed version required for compatibility in the electronic format of submitted deliverables.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836286</data>
</node>
<node id="Current Contractor">
  <data key="d0">Current Contractor</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Current Contractor is required to commence demobilization and support the transition 90 days prior to the completion of the contract term.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Follow-On Contractor">
  <data key="d0">Follow-On Contractor</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Follow-On Contractor receives support from the current contractor during the 90-day transition period post-mobilization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Cd-Rom">
  <data key="d0">Cd-Rom</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Cd-Rom is an alternative submission method for deliverables when email file size limits are exceeded.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Option for Increased Quantity">
  <data key="d0">Option for Increased Quantity</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Option for Increased Quantity is a clause that allows orders issued during the contract's effective period to be completed afterward, governing rights and obligations as if completed within the period, with no deliveries required after the contract completion date or final task order completion date.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Option to Extend Services">
  <data key="d0">Option to Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Option to Extend Services is a clause permitting the Government to require continued performance of services within contract limits and rates, adjustable only by labor rate revisions, exercisable multiple times up to a total of 6 months, via written notice prior to expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Option to Extend the Term of the Contract">
  <data key="d0">Option to Extend the Term of the Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Option to Extend the Term of the Contract is a clause allowing the Government to extend the contract term by written notice prior to completion of the current period, with preliminary notice 30 days before expiration, not committing to extension, and total duration not exceeding 96 months including options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns is a clause adding a 10 percent factor to offers except for HUBZone small business concerns not waiving preference and certain small business offers, applied on a line item basis after other factors, with award preference to HUBZone when tied with large business.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation">
  <data key="d0">Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation is a clause requiring contractors to rerepresent size and socioeconomic status upon events like novation, merger, or for long-term contracts, validating in SAM or submitting forms, defining terms like long-term contract and small business concern.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires">
  <data key="d0">Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires is a clause identifying classes of service employees and stating wages and fringe benefits as if employed by the contracting agency under 5 U.S.C. 5341 or 5 U.S.C. 332, for information only and not a wage determination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Certification of Final Indirect Costs">
  <data key="d0">Certification of Final Indirect Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Certification of Final Indirect Costs is a clause requiring contractors to certify proposals for final indirect cost rates using a specified format signed by a vice president or chief financial officer, with failure leading to unilateral rates by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Clauses Incorporated by Reference">
  <data key="d0">Clauses Incorporated by Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clauses Incorporated by Reference is a clause incorporating clauses with the same force as full text, available upon request or electronically at specified addresses including acquisition.gov and others.&lt;SEP&gt;Clauses Incorporated by Reference is a FAR clause that incorporates one or more clauses by reference with the same force and effect as full text, available upon request from the Contracting Officer or electronically at specified addresses including https://acquisition.gov/browse/index/far, http://farsite.hill.af.mil/vmdfara.htm, and http://www.secnav.navy.mil/rda/Pages/NMCARS.aspx.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Alterations in Contract">
  <data key="d0">Alterations in Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Alterations in Contract is a clause stating portions of the contract are altered as specified.&lt;SEP&gt;Alterations in Contract is a FAR clause that specifies portions of the contract are altered as indicated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Authorized Deviations in Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Authorized Deviations in Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Authorized Deviations in Clauses is a clause indicating use of FAR or DFARS clauses with deviations by adding (DEVIATION) after the date or regulation name.&lt;SEP&gt;Authorized Deviations in Clauses is a FAR clause that indicates the use of any Federal Acquisition Regulation clause with an authorized deviation by adding "(DEVIATION)" after the date, and similarly for Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Limitation of Government's Obligation">
  <data key="d0">Limitation of Government's Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Limitation of Government's Obligation is a DFARS clause for incrementally funded contract line items, with allotted funds specified on task orders, and contractor performance up to the point of available funds.&lt;SEP&gt;Limitation of Government's Obligation is a DFARS clause addressing incrementally funded contract line items, including fund allotments, performance limits, notifications to the Contracting Officer, equitable adjustments, and termination provisions under the Termination for Convenience of the Government clause.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HUBZone Small Business Concern is a qualified small business under HUBZone program, eligible for evaluation preferences unless waived, required to perform at least 40 percent of joint venture work beyond administrative functions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Small Business Concern is an independently owned and operated entity not dominant in its field, qualified under 13 CFR part 121 size standards, including affiliates determined by control factors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Secretary of Labor">
  <data key="d0">Secretary of Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Secretary of Labor provides revisions to prevailing labor rates for adjusting extension rates under Option to Extend Services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="System for Award Management">
  <data key="d0">System for Award Management</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">System for Award Management is the platform where contractors validate or update representations and certifications for rerepresentation.&lt;SEP&gt;System for Award Management requires complete representations and certifications under FAR 52.204-7, or individual submissions if not complete.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Acquisition Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Federal Acquisition Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal Acquisition Regulation governs cost principles, clauses, and supplements applicable to contracts, with deviations indicated by (DEVIATION).&lt;SEP&gt;Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) is referenced as 48 CFR Chapter 1, with clauses incorporated by reference and deviations indicated.&lt;SEP&gt;Federal Acquisition Regulation is the regulatory framework from which FAR clauses are incorporated by reference or full text in Section K of the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement">
  <data key="d0">Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement includes clauses with authorized deviations indicated by (DEVIATION).&lt;SEP&gt;Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement (DFARS) is referenced as 48 CFR, with clauses like 252.232-7007 and deviations indicated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="North American Industry Classification System">
  <data key="d0">North American Industry Classification System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">North American Industry Classification System provides codes and size standards for determining small business status, accessible at sba.gov.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Long-term Contract">
  <data key="d0">Long-term Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Long-term Contract means a contract of more than five years in duration, including options, but excluding extensions not exceeding six months under 52.217-8 or similar authority.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Affiliates">
  <data key="d0">Affiliates</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Affiliates refers to business concerns where one directly or indirectly controls or has the power to control others, or a third party controls them, based on factors like common ownership, management, and contractual relationships per 13 CFR 121.103.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Joint Venture">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Joint Venture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HUBZone Joint Venture requires that at least 40 percent of the aggregate work performed be completed by the HUBZone small business parties, exceeding administrative functions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Women-Owned Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Women-Owned Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Women-Owned Small Business Concern is a small business concern owned by women, including joint ventures eligible under the WOSB Program per 13 CFR 127.506.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Economically Disadvantaged Women-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Economically Disadvantaged Women-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Economically Disadvantaged Women-Owned Small Business is a women-owned small business with economic disadvantage, including compliant joint ventures per 13 CFR 127.506.&lt;SEP&gt;Economically Disadvantaged Women-Owned Small Business is a set-aside category applicable to the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Veteran-Owned Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Veteran-Owned Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Veteran-Owned Small Business Concern is a small business concern owned by veterans, including service-disabled variants.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business Concern is a small business owned by service-disabled veterans, eligible under the SDVOSB Program per 13 CFR 128.402, including joint ventures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Disadvantaged Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Small Disadvantaged Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Small Disadvantaged Business Concern is defined in 13 CFR 124.1001 as a small business with social and economic disadvantage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I">
  <data key="d0">Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I substitutes paragraph (h)(1) to require representation of small business size status for each NAICS code assigned to the contract, such as NAICS 561210 with size standard $47,000,000.00.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
<node id="Novation Agreement">
  <data key="d0">Novation Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Novation Agreement is a contract modification that transfers rights and obligations, triggering rerepresentation within 30 days under Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836287</data>
</node>
