<node id="Termination for Convenience of the Government">
  <data key="d0">Termination for Convenience of the Government</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Termination for Convenience of the Government is a clause referenced multiple times in Limitation of Government's Obligation, governing the Government's right to terminate contract line items and limiting reimbursement to allotted funds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836289</data>
</node>
<node id="Disputes">
  <data key="d0">Disputes</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Disputes is a clause referenced in Limitation of Government's Obligation, treating failure to agree on equitable adjustments as a dispute concerning a question of fact.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836289</data>
</node>
<node id="Default">
  <data key="d0">Default</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Default is a clause whose Government rights are not limited by the termination provisions in Limitation of Government's Obligation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836289</data>
</node>
<node id="31 U.S.C. 1342">
  <data key="d0">31 U.S.C. 1342</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">31 U.S.C. 1342 is a statute prohibiting the acceptance of voluntary services, referenced in Limitation of Government's Obligation as not authorizing such services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836289</data>
</node>
