  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Limits of Liability (LOL) are required in multiple annexes, sub-annexes, and spec items, necessitating an understanding of their application.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836290</data>
</node>
<node id="Unit Price Labor (UPL)">
  <data key="d0">Unit Price Labor (UPL)</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Unit Price Labor (UPL) requires a rate for one hour of work-in-place for work over limits of liability and other over-and-above work, encompassing all applicable costs without post-award renegotiation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836290</data>
</node>
<node id="Risk Mitigation">
  <data key="d0">Risk Mitigation</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Risk Mitigation involves practical contingency plans to address shortages of materials, equipment, and workers during contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836290</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 3">
  <data key="d0">Factor 3</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 3 evaluates the offeror's technical approach, including staffing levels, methodology for performance objectives, systems approach, limits of liability, supply chain, and risk mitigation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836290</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 4 Small Business Utilization and Participation">
  <data key="d0">Factor 4 Small Business Utilization and Participation</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 4 assesses historical small business utilization and proposed participation commitment, requiring at least 20% small business involvement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836290</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 5 Safety">
  <data key="d0">Factor 5 Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 5 evaluates safety through DART rates, TCR rates, and a technical approach to safety management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759836290</data>
</node>
<node id="Performance Work Statement (PWS)">
  <data key="d0">Performance Work Statement (PWS)</data>
  <data key="d1">statement_of_work</data>
